==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یامیام|tr=yamyam}} meaning also “[[Niam-Niam]]”, an obsolete name used by 18th- and 19th-century French and British travellers for the {{w|Azande}}, an ethnic group of North Central Africa. The name is said to mean “great eaters” in the {{der|tr|din|-}} language, supposedly referring to cannibalistic propensities formerly ascribed to the Azande.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tr|[jɑm.ˈjɑm]}}
===Noun===
{{head|tr|noun}}
# [[cannibal]]
